<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Merkvah</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-25 11:30:34</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Qman,<BR>
<BR>
A)  Yes, the weapon is all it is said to be.  The defensive bonus of using a shild, along with the interrupting bonus of bash, in many people's eyes, more than makes up for the loss of damage from a 2h weapon.<BR>
B)  At lvl 4, you should be looking for fine steel or forged weapons, but really, normal or even rusty will be fine for a while.  At lvl 4, I was usign a FS 2h sword that I paid 10 pp for, and it was ideal for that level.  If you go to U Guk and get a GB, it will not be you who does it.  There is a certain ammount of honor in camping it yourself (yes, Verant screwed us in the honor category with this weapon, but if you just lay that aside...  make up a new storyline or something - Shin Lord is insane or somethin)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
While the camp is very easy (as I have said above) it would be suicide for a low level like that... except for the guy who brought his lvl 51 wizzie friend with Ice Comet, but hey, who actually earned that blade?<BR>
<BR>
I earned mine.<BR>
<BR>
Merkvah Holyblade<BR>
Paladin of Tunare<BR>
Tallon Zek</font></td></tr></table>
