<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Mesaoyatun</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-09 17:15:44</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Not only is the Ghoulbane a fine weapon & necessary for the Fiery Avenger quest later on, but I am told that the weapon is also needed for the Shadow Knight's "particle weapon" as well.<BR>
<BR>
We will now have to compete with High Level SK's camping the weapon as well as other farmers & such.<BR>
<BR>
As far as lost honor in facing the Shin Lord goes, he is a fallen paladin & a member of a barbaric race.<BR>
<BR>
The Frogloks skin their prisoners alive. (explaining the Troll-Hide Belt & Elf-Skin Gloves)  If they were a civilized race, they would merely kill their prisoners & be done with it.<BR>
<BR>
The blood on the altars of the Froglok Priest's room proves that they engage in the ritual sacrifice of sentient beings.<BR>
<BR>
Though their victims may be Trolls, such acts are abhorrent to knights of any code.  I will see to it that the Shin Lord is defeated & the blade used for the greater glory of Prexus.  <BR>
<BR>
I shall aid the Frogloks despite their nature by facing off against the minions of the Ghoul Lord as well.  I am an inquisitor of the Deepwater Knights & they must suffer my righteous judgment.</font></td></tr></table>
